# ============================================================
# .gitignore — Files Git Should NEVER Track
# ============================================================
#
# Place this file in your ROOT folder: ResumeAnalyser/.gitignore
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
# Some files/folders should NEVER be uploaded to GitHub:
# - venv/ = thousands of files, recreatable with pip install
# - node_modules/ = thousands of files, recreatable with npm install
# - .env = contains secrets (API keys, passwords)
# - uploads/ = user-uploaded files (privacy + size)
# - __pycache__/ = Python bytecode cache, not source code
# - dist/ = built frontend (Vercel builds this itself)
#
# Git reads this file and automatically skips these paths.
# ============================================================

# ---- Python ----
backend/venv/
backend/__pycache__/
backend/*.pyc
backend/*.pyo
backend/uploads/*
!backend/uploads/.gitkeep
# The !.gitkeep means: ignore all uploads EXCEPT this one
# empty placeholder file (so Git tracks the folder exists)

# ---- Node / React ----
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/dist/
frontend/.env.local

# ---- Environment Files ----
# Keep .env.production (it has no secrets, just a URL)
# but never commit files with real API keys or passwords
backend/.env
frontend/.env
# Uncomment above if your .env files ever contain secrets

# ---- OS Files ----
.DS_Store          # Mac folder metadata
Thumbs.db          # Windows thumbnail cache
desktop.ini        # Windows folder settings

# ---- VS Code ----
.vscode/settings.json
# (you CAN commit .vscode/extensions.json if you want
#  to recommend extensions to teammates)

# ---- Logs ----
*.log
npm-debug.log*